be an infection or a chronic condition.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03832,0.077866,0.097374,0.114,0.10351,0.09879,0.10093,0.090268,0.08148,0.086305,0.062703,0.048455],"unified_progress":[0.038529,0.078073,0.094963,0.10622,0.10247,0.098684,0.10051,0.096906,0.089622,0.084733,0.066004,0.043282]},{"section":6,"text":"He's also reporting polyuria and polydipsia.","dimension":9,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.061173,0.12557,0.11248,0.1062,0.092736,0.086265,0.084845,0.077225,0.070888,0.066101,0.062143,0.054381],"unified_progress":[0.077565,0.11158,0.10088,0.094691,0.092967,0.090163,0.084824,0.086669,0.078679,0.071049,0.06169,0.049239]},{"section":7,"text":"Those are symptoms of hyperglycemia, but I should consider other possibilities too.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.054603,0.086334,0.098076,0.11016,0.099889,0.095136,0.094616,0.08558,0.07947,0.07929,0.065767,0.051078],"unified_progress":[0.04927,0.081261,0.094082,0.10476,0.10167,0.097214,0.097646,0.091499,0.085003,0.082995,0.06627,0.048324]},{"section":8,"text":"Maybe it's related to his kidneys since he's also having back pain, which could be from kidney issues.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046774,0.07547,0.090866,0.10074,0.098471,0.096864,0.099021,0.093022,0.086852,0.08794,0.069744,0.054235],"unified_progress":[0.048002,0.078179,0.090869,0.098496,0.099448,0.097384,0.098762,0.096845,0.090258,0.084855,0.068767,0.048135]},{"section":9,"text":"Looking at the lab results: hypoalbuminemia means low albumin levels, which can be seen in conditions like nephrotic syndrome or chronic kidney disease.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036761,0.068669,0.093217,0.10661,0.11063,0.10787,0.10568,0.093366,0.083533,0.079423,0.063391,0.050851],"unified_progress":[0.040174,0.076637,0.094233,0.10276,0.10557,0.1014,0.10043,0.094698,0.088735,0.080945,0.066539,0.04788]},{"section":10,"text":"The mild anemia could be due to blood loss or decreased production, and the thrombocytopenia suggests a problem with his platelets or bone marrow.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038669,0.06586,0.091938,0.10748,0.11464,0.11409,0.11438,0.095682,0.082303,0.070893,0.058156,0.045907],"unified_progress":[0.042837,0.076373,0.094232,0.10313,0.10808,0.10361,0.10405,0.093306,0.088347,0.076006,0.063147,0.046886]},{"section":11,"text":"The serum electrophoresis shows a monoclonal Igk peak.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028084,0.063333,0.091724,0.11183,0.1208,0.12305,0.11871,0.10369,0.082662,0.064187,0.051589,0.04035],"unified_progress":[0.033928,0.075097,0.096601,0.10951,0.1151,0.10745,0.10368,0.09268,0.093118,0.070467,0.056585,0.045784]},{"section":12,"text":"Monoclonal proteins in the blood are often seen in multiple myeloma, which is a type of cancer, specifically plasma cell disorder.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029549,0.052941,0.075515,0.091225,0.10502,0.11101,0.11404,0.10963,0.10035,0.086183,0.067157,0.057375],"unified_progress":[0.032494,0.062449,0.08364,0.098376,0.10193,0.12433,0.10778,0.09952,0.091363,0.08264,0.065887,0.049594]},{"section":13,"text":"The bone marrow biopsy showing plasma cell foci that make up 18% of hematopoietic cells supports this.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028547,0.057905,0.08497,0.10481,0.11504,0.1191,0.11802,0.10676,0.087825,0.070047,0.058928,0.048057],"unified_progress":[0.034652,0.071815,0.092405,0.10429,0.1117,0.10673,0.10248,0.095119,0.09524,0.074101,0.061138,0.050339]},{"section":14,"text":"Plasma cells are a key part of multiple myeloma.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033073,0.054351,0.073687,0.087225,0.099915,0.10648,0.10915,0.10707,0.099686,0.087903,0.073636,0.067827],"unified_progress":[0.035746,0.062797,0.081177,0.094184,0.098267,0.11618,0.10357,0.097803,0.092573,0.084813,0.072214,0.060677]},{"section":15,"text":"The urinalysis shows 4+ proteinuria, which is a lot of protein in the urine.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035359,0.062697,0.087795,0.10329,0.11204,0.1135,0.11103,0.098974,0.086389,0.072524,0.063137,0.05326],"unified_progress":[0.041174,0.074788,0.092065,0.1014,0.1069,0.10279,0.10044,0.093496,0.091048,0.076465,0.06581,0.053623]},{"section":16,"text":"This could be due to the kidneys filtering too much protein, which is common in conditions like nephrotic syndrome.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04294,0.056287,0.077837,0.092401,0.10169,0.10556,0.10836,0.10285,0.095588,0.08707,0.070551,0.058863],"unified_progress":[0.043099,0.066987,0.08549,0.096564,0.10082,0.10773,0.10413,0.098345,0.091726,0.084135,0.069228,0.05174]},{"section":17,"text":"But given the presence of the monoclonal Igk, it's more likely related to the plasma cell disorder affecting the kidneys.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.050459,0.052349,0.069779,0.080569,0.087365,0.091887,0.095645,0.095857,0.094768,0.095632,0.09198,0.09371],"unified_progress":[0.048156,0.061958,0.074146,0.083229,0.088611,0.092478,0.09304,0.095079,0.094283,0.091781,0.08998,0.087258]},{"section":18,"text":"Putting it all together: the combination of plasma cell foci in the bone marrow, monoclonal Igk, and proteinuria points towards multiple myeloma.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.021533,0.034921,0.046825,0.055021,0.060243,0.066093,0.071882,0.081335,0.091457,0.10992,0.14383,0.21694],"unified_progress":[0.02056,0.035491,0.045872,0.05622,0.060751,0.071737,0.075121,0.086197,0.098589,0.10527,0.144,0.2002]},{"section":19,"text":"The back pain could be from the lesions in the vertebrae, which is a common manifestation of myeloma.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037446,0.043712,0.056611,0.06