sions, or maybe the light chains affecting the kidneys.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029859,0.065481,0.079041,0.089088,0.097422,0.1013,0.10417,0.099704,0.094056,0.08871,0.082047,0.069124],"unified_progress":[0.034375,0.055811,0.073145,0.078514,0.089758,0.099658,0.099927,0.10051,0.1005,0.09907,0.09387,0.074858]},{"section":13,"text":"The anemia and thrombocytopenia are likely from bone marrow infiltration by the plasma cells, crowding out other blood cells.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032568,0.069316,0.081902,0.089892,0.095011,0.098003,0.10027,0.097365,0.094427,0.08889,0.081559,0.070799],"unified_progress":[0.034785,0.05966,0.074238,0.082851,0.092378,0.09766,0.10089,0.098755,0.099385,0.096793,0.089408,0.073196]},{"section":14,"text":"Hypoalbuminemia might be due to liver issues, but more likely the protein loss in urine (nephrotic syndrome from myeloma).","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028592,0.063645,0.078197,0.088084,0.095316,0.099069,0.10301,0.099965,0.096068,0.091205,0.084887,0.071955],"unified_progress":[0.031445,0.055163,0.071148,0.079284,0.090253,0.097654,0.10156,0.10059,0.10181,0.10045,0.094456,0.076185]},{"section":15,"text":"The 18% plasma cells in bone marrow is significant; I remember that over 10% is a criteria for myeloma.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036679,0.076615,0.090753,0.096093,0.096634,0.09534,0.095967,0.092357,0.088978,0.08458,0.076839,0.069167],"unified_progress":[0.040473,0.071306,0.085247,0.092883,0.098287,0.097905,0.10271,0.09351,0.090312,0.084512,0.077156,0.065695]},{"section":16,"text":"Also, the presence of lytic lesions (CRAB features: hyperCalcemia, Renal failure, Anemia, Bone lesions) meets the myeloma criteria.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03235,0.069177,0.082582,0.091187,0.096427,0.098392,0.099853,0.095644,0.091663,0.089432,0.080784,0.072507],"unif